< text>
This is an okay wash. It's not expensive, they have free vacuums, and they have a vending machine which has detailing stuff for decent prices. The wash doesn't always get everything off  of your car but it's worth it if want to keep your car pretty clean and get it done quickly. My only complaint with this place is that the wash has torn clear coat off my car. And not small amounts either. I just got this car, I did a very thorough check of the cars condition before I bought it. This damage wasn't present before I started taking it here, and it gets worse every time I go. Granted, it's a six year old car but as I said this damage wasn't present before I started taking it here. Now I have to conjure up the money to get it fixed before it gets even worse, it'd be awesome if the owners would fix the damage, if they do I'll add that to my review. My advice to anyone reading this is to only use this wash when you need a quick wash, and hand wash your car more often than you take it here. If you don't care about your cars condition, take it here as much as you'd like. But I wouldn't recommend taking your car here more than once every two weeks. Hand washing is best!</text>

< review>
This place is great don't let the bad reviews from others distract you from the fact that this Surf Thru Express, doesn't get as packed as the other one in town. It's a no brainer that you obviously don't want to bring a new car here haha. Like the workers in the front actually scrub down your car before you enter the machine. They make sure to walk with your car as it start to enter and even scrub the back as you enter. The place is very clean and well maintained, sometimes they walk through the vacuum section and if they notice your car didn't get well scrubbed they'll ask you to go ahead and go around for another wash for free! It happened to me 2 times since I've been coming here. In conclusion don't believe the bad reviews that complain this place is great and doesn't get as busy. I highly recommend you try it out for your own thoughts.</review>

< review>
We purchased vinyl plank flooring for our whole home except for a bathroom and a closet from Michael Flooring. We also chose to have them install the flooring. Initially, during the sales process, Mason, our sales guy, was very helpful, friendly, etc. we actually selected this company out of the several others because of the selection and customer service. HUGE mistake. The problems began during the installation process and hasn‚Äôt ended yet.

We has numerous issues during the installation process. First, the wrong flooring was installed in our laundry room that we didn‚Äôt see until it has already been installed. Second, the installers permanently damaged the lid to our toilet when they removed it to install the bathroom floors. They never mentioned it or apologized for it. We initially thought it was just dirty, but after cleaning it, realized the paint was scraped off. Another issue was the product that was to be installed around the base of our kitchen cabinets. Mason was extremely confusing during the purchasing process regarding this, but he ultimately promised that a white base shoe/toe kick material would be installed, going as far as guaranteeing it would not be the flooring toe kick that would be installed. Well, the installers installed the flooring toe kick which was not supposed to happen according to Mason but was normal according to the installers. After a harrowing exchange with Mason, we were able to get actual wooden baseboard installed along the outside of the cabinets (which Mason said couldn‚Äôt be done initially during the sales process).

Those issues, although annoying, are not the problem. Flash forward 6 months after installation, and now we are dealing with water damage in our kitchen because during the installation process, the installers moved our dishwasher and didn‚Äôt pay attention to the fact that the plastic main drain pipe moved underneath the frame causing it to crack and water to leak underneath the floors to the point that water was seeping up through the cracks in puddles. We rarely use the dishwasher (maybe 2-3 times in the past 6 months) which is why we are barely finding it about this issue. After contacting Michael Flooring twice asking to speak the the owner who apparently refuses to speak to us, we had to deal with Mason again. He is so unpleasant to deal with regarding issues. He makes passive aggressive comments, he‚Äôs argumentative, and deflective of any responsibility. Of course during the installation process he blamed all the issues on the installers when some of the issues were his communication errors. As usual, as soon as I told Mason about the water damage, he immediately began denying that the dishwasher was touched during the installation process, even though he wasn‚Äôt present to supervise and didn‚Äôt listen or ask any questions to understand that it had to be moved to demo the tile underneath and install the new floors, which we have evidence that proves this. After reviewing all our evidence of this (including the diagnostics from the dishwasher repairman who told us it was damaged during the installation process) and the fact that if the crack were there prior to the installation process, it would have leaked prior and they would have seen water damage during the installation process which they acknowledged was true, Mason denied that they caused the crack saying it was there prior and refuses to repair the damaged flooring and pad. Interesting he asserts this when a repairman diagnosed otherwise.

So, I know this is a long review, but I would feel horribly if someone else were to experience this after paying thousands of dollars. I was hoping that Michael Flooring would exceed my low expectations and at the very least and just fix the damage to the floor since I already fixed the damage to the dishwasher. Unfortunately, they are only pleasant during the sales process. Knowing what I do now, I would have paid more money to another company to have had a better experience. It‚Äôs unfortunate that companies will lie to customers and negate responsibility for a dollar.< /review>

<Text>When in Buena Park looking for a decent bar with very good Korean bar food, this is the place to go. Beer selection as well as Korean wines and liquor are available. < Review>
One of the last Korean bars in the area. The OG pine tree is gone, minsok Chon been gone like 20 times, and I don't want to go-to Hawaiian Gardens.

They have the right kind of chicken beer soju combos although I don't like how they butterfly the chicken, but that's because new school I suppose.

I usually end up here every time I'm back in the LA / Orange County area. Great place to catch up with the old crew.< /Review>

<Name>Diana Chen</Name><Date>1582405438365<//Date><rating>5< /rating>< Text>
I think I‚Äôve just had the best Mexican food of my life here.  It makes me seriously consider moving to Berkeley.  And I ordered huevos rancheros. Not exciting, right?  Wrong!  Each component of the dish was excellent on its own, from the flavorful bed of black beans, to the lightly fried homemade tortillas, to the fried eggs, and the spicy spoonful of thick salsa on top.  Together, it was so delicious and comforting.  The food here is obviously made with care, and you can taste and feel it.

I couldn‚Äôt just try one dish, so I also ordered the tortilla soup, which was also very enjoyable.  It would be great to order for takeout if you are sick.  It‚Äôs a huge portion and I‚Äôd suggest sharing, so you can eat another dish.  There are so many things to try on the menu.

I also ordered the horchata, which is now my favorite horchata, because it is not too sweet. I can drink it without my tastebuds being overstimulated by sugar.

Prices are very reasonable, service is great, and the food is incredible.  I can‚Äôt wait to come back and try more items on the menu.< /Text>

<Date>1423354551739</Date><text>Two hours after leaving Los Cilantros I still have the sound of satisfaction resonating through my system.  The sweet feeling of having had a home cooked meal where you don't skimp on the quality of the ingredients.  The sensation that I just had the very best possible with the added southern Mexican, spicy, balmy flavor from Oaxacan terroir.  Authentic Southern Mexican cuisine!  The food is testy! Best tacos, best tamales ever! Their mole sublime! When you bite into the chicken you know it was a healthy chicken with texture and flavor.  The white corn masa sweetness is incomparable, and organic!  The place is calm and very comfortable with big, sturdy, wooden tables and seats. Spacious but not chi-chi or pretentious and the personnel cordial and courteous. <Review>This is the kind of home cooked food that taps into memories of my best  childhood meals. The flavors of each dish are complex and satisfying. From the spicy, smokey mole enchiladas, to barbacoa that melts in your mouth, to the tender saucy chicken tinga tacos. The brunch dishes are what you might find at many Mexican restaurants, but at Los Cilantros they have been perfected. < review>
Just saw my first movie back in theaters and I loved it here, it was clean and the employees were friendly. I easily purchased my ticket onsite at one of their kiosk machines then proceeded to theater. Their prices are shockingly good compared to other movie locations in the city, I also couldn't believe the low prices of the concessions were. I'm not sure if the prices will stay this low, but for now I'll enjoy it as much as I can. My only complaint is that the seats don't recline back as far as I'd like and they're a little hard, but surely they'll get softer as they get broken in more.  It feels great to be back at the theater.< /review>

< Text>
i purchased my parking pass the day before dropping my vehicle off and it's a pretty good price. i'm sure there are closer locations or better prices but the reason i purchased at this parking garage is because of the shuttle. they were quick getting us to the terminal and back to the parking garage as well. it does fill up quickly though so be sure to make your reservation ahead of time.<//Text>

<time>1622000444748<//time><rate>5</rate><Review>I have parked my car at the Parking Spot for years and like the service and sense that my car is safe and will be waiting for me just as I left it when I return.  A recent visit found me limping into the garage with a flat tire with little time to spare to catch my flight.  The valet parking attendant told me not to worry, they would put the car safely away and I could deal with it on my return.  I asked whether they could arrange to have the flat replaced with my spare tire and to add the cost to my bill.  The attendant said he would try.

When I returned, I was dreading that it might take me some time to sort out the problem.  I was happily surprised to find my car waiting for me with the spare tire installed at no charge.   I inquired about the replacement of the tire and was told the employees took it upon themselves to change it.   It was a pleasure to leave a tip in appreciation and gratitude.  A business that provides a reliable level of good service, yet can still surprise with exceptional assistance that goes above and beyond, will always have my patronage.<//Review>< pictures>

<Name>Dmitriy Mykalo (Dillon)</Name><Review>Fast and convenient
Spacious and clean parking lot with indoor and outdoor spaces. The main advantage of this place is not in the garage itself, but in the shuttles. They are clean and most importantly regular. On my previous trip I used another parking lot and upon arrival I was waiting for the shuttle for about an hour, that day I counted that the yellow shuttles go more often than others.</Review></record>

<user>104325761077908679943< /user><user_name>Mary Delgado< /user_name><Date>1622597402997</Date>< Rating>

<text>I have to admit I was a bit hesitant to book since there are so many mixed reviews online but I'm so glad I did.  Everything was completely easy and smooth.  I booked everything online and downloaded the app as an extra way to keep organized.  The drop off was a complete breeze. A shuttle was waiting for us the moment we stepped out of the elevator and dropped us off right outside of our terminal. Upon our return I used the app to get the shuttle to pick us up.  The app is really great and shows you in live time where the shuttles are so you're not guessing how much longer it will be. You can literally follow the dots along the map as they move through the route.  I will definitely be booking again.  No more dealing with rideshare waiting times and outrageous price hikes during "Peak" hours.<//text>< Pictures>

< Name>

<time>1620515620426<//time><rate>5</rate><text>Parking in LA is expensive.  That's a given.  LA can also be a callous place as far as service is concerned, having lived there many years, I've come to expect as much.  So after my wife and I both convened at LAX, both coming in from separate long trips to return to our car and then drive 4 hours north, we were not expecting to be treated so kindly by the shuttle driver that would bring us back to the Century Blvd garage.  I wish I had thought to ask his name.  First, I saw the shuttle and waived.  He saw me and pointed to where he was going to stop (which was about 50 yards from where we were).  To my disbelief he graciously remained there as it took me about a minute to jog to his location (I thought for sure he'd stop and then press on before my wife caught up to me).  He was so kind and thoughtful, he made sure he dropped us off close to where our car would be and then let us know how we could apply our AAA discount.  It's the little things you know? I used The Parking Spot LAX on Century December 8th-10th and had absolutely no problems. I made my reservations using their app, arrived and self-parked on the rooftop with ease. < review>
Recent new Spot Club member here and had my first experience Dec 2020 at the Century location. I usually park at the Hilton, Westin, Marriott, but came across Parking Spot and decided to try them out.

My first experience I opted for the rooftop but when I checked in one of the attendants said it was fine to park in one of the covered spots, which I did. When I returned I was surprised my parking fee was higher so I addressed this with David the manager at Century. He explained that his attendant was wrong for giving me that direction and said I have to park on the roof next time as there's another gate there. He was very accommodating and friendly and professional and was able to credit me my earlier rooftop estimate.

I also like Parking Spot bc you can track with the mobile app the pickup vans at LAX, which I wasn't able to do with Hilton, Westin, Marriott.

I'm a fan of Parking Spot and the Century and would recommend this location.<//review>

<text>My one tip: Use their app to make a reservation for their valet service.  Until pricing changes their valet rate is almost the same as their no-reservation-covered parking rate.

Their shuttles are distinctive and easily recognizable so you can see them coming from a distance.

<Review>Easy in. Easy out. Friendly, helpful employees. The Parking Spot is a safe, relatively inexpensive place to park your car. Roof parking is less expensive than inside, lower-floor parking.  Free, comfortable bus service to and from LAX.  Board The Parking Spot's yellow, polka dot bus curbside, in front of "Baggage Claim."  Make sure the bus you take goes to the lot where you parked. There are a number of The Parking Spot garages. This review describes the Century Boulevard structure.  While you are on your trip, the car can be detailed.  It nice to come home to a shiny, clean car.  Discount are usually available on the internet; check their website. One nice touch; they give the driver and passengers free bottles of chilled water.<//Review></record></dataset><record>

< rate>
5<//rate>
<Text>It is my opinion that this is the place to park when you go to Los Angeles airport. It is not the cheapest. It is however totally convenient. The entrance is on Century Boulevard and you can register with the parking spot and get a pass card. You pull in did you take your information and you get on a shuttle bus. That takes approximately 325 minutes. You take the shuttle bus to your gate and they give you a ticket you have the choice of parking on the roof doing self parking or valet parking. I always choose valet parking, it is only a dollar or two more and completely convenient. When you come back, you make sure you get on the right parking spot bus there is a Sepulveda one as well as the Century Boulevard one and you go back to the parking spot. If you have the liepard you will have already given the driver your ticket and your car will be waiting for you. By the way you do collect points if you go there a lot.</Text>< Pics>
None</Pics>

<user>111061711270254530442< /user><Name>Cathy Battaglia<//Name><Time>1484416870376<//Time><rate>5</rate>< text>
Although there were long lines of cars when I arrived (the day before Christmas), things were handled. Wry smoothly and efficiently.  I was able to catch the 3rd shuttle to the airport, with very little waiting in line.  When I returned, I called the number on my ticket and a shuttle came within a few minutes.  When I arrived at the Parking Spot, my car was waiting at the curb.  They took my suitcase from the shuttle and put it into my trunk, while I paid at the window (which only took a few moments).  Definitely my best experience at getting to and from LAX.  Thank you for making this such a painless experience!<//text>

< Review>
It's pricer than other parking lots but I wouldn't want to go cheap on a parking garage.  We have and we have paid with time and agony.  There's no question I would pay a little extra for the many shuttles they have and how they just streamline everything(dropping off, car wash even, and picking up)!

I don't go anywhere else and let the Spot take care and worry about parking.  I've learned from my mistakes and if you know ahead of time reserve your spot to save even more time and money.<//Review>

< Pics>
None</Pics>
< Text>
Have been parking here for more than 4 years when traveling via LAX. Witnessed the shuttle bus upgrades a few years back, and more recently the pickup spot change to upper level. Parking at LAX is not great and many off airport options exist.  The Parking Spot has two at Century and Sepulveda. They can sometimes fill up and during off hours you can wait for a shuttle bus pickup. The new Parking Spot app helps somewhat with bus location but GPS and data nearby major airports like LAX is spotty at best. Cost can be high at over 20 per night. Valet is only 1 dollar more per night typically. Free water is a nice touch. Wish the price was slightly lower and buses ran more frequently. Continuing legal conflicts with LAX will likely make future years interesting as parking situation changes and lawsuits go forward.<//Text>
